<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Tottenham have held talks over a deal for Inter Milan defender Milan Skriniar, 25, but remain some way apart on valuation with the Italians asking for £52m.</p>

<p>Technical director Steve Hitchen was in Milan in Wednesday for talks with Skriniar’s representatives.</p>

<p>Tottenham reportedly attempted to include Tanguy Ndombele as part of a deal but Inter Milan are not interested in the midfielder. </p>

<p>Tottenham are in talks with Inter Milan over Milan Skriniar but are yet to agree a deal</p>

<p>Skriniar fell out of favour at Inter towards the end of last season and the 25-year-old may be tempted by the prospect of regular playing time at Tottenham.</p>

<p>Since joining Inter in 2016, Skriniar has 128 appearances for the club. </p>

<p>Tottenham are eager to bring in a centre-back with Jose Mourinho determined for his side to be more resilient at the back.</p>

<p>Tottenham manager Jose Mourinho is determined for his side to bring in a new centre-back</p>

<p>The north London club have been heavily active during this transfer window, bringing Gareth Bale back on loan while also signing Pierre-Emile Hojbjerg, Joe Hart, Matt Doherty and Sergio Reguilon.</p>

<p>Tottenham can call upon the likes of Toby Alderweireld, Davinson Sanchez and Eric Dier as centre-back options, while they also have youngster Japhet Tanganga at their disposal. </p>
